<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">H Tile Strategy</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Pair with power tiles:</span> H combines with Z (HAZEL, HAZE), X (HEX, HOAX), J (HAJ), and K (HOOK, HAWK) for massive point density. Prioritise these combos over common words.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use digraph hooks:</span> Adding H before existing words creates hooks — SH+OW=SHOW, CH+AMP=CHAMP, TH+AT=THAT. Check the board for words you can front-hook with H digraphs.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Premium square targeting:</span> At 4 points base, H on a double-letter becomes 8 points from a single tile. Place H on DLS whenever possible — it's worth more than most tiles on premium squares.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">H Digraph Power Plays</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
  <p class="text-base text-gray-200">H forms <span class="text-white font-medium">four major digraphs</span> in English: SH, TH, CH, and WH. Each creates hundreds of valid words. Knowing which digraph your rack supports is the first step to maximising H's 4-point contribution.</p>
</div>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
